s14400:09:03,554 --> 00:09:08,379including strategies, to deliver an effective intervention14500:09:08,561 --> 00:09:11,561in new settings, other than where it was previously tested for effectiveness14600:09:15,423 --> 00:09:21,861and/or, within broader populations under real-world conditions.14700:09:22,350 --> 00:09:26,125Such efforts include getting the effective intervention14800:09:26,306 --> 00:09:29,969adopted, sustained, and scaled up.14900:09:30,189 --> 00:09:32,164I hope that was clear.15000:09:32,400 --> 00:09:36,775Specific outcomes may relate, for instance15100:09:36,972 --> 00:09:43,060to acceptability, sustainability, compliance, appropriateness,15200:09:43,270 --> 00:09:47,145penetration, or coverage, and so on.15300:09:48,283 --> 00:09:53,471It is critical that these outcomes take account of the context15400:09:53,676 --> 00:09:57,388and this point then links us back to all the concepts15500:09:57,581 --> 00:10:01,069that have been addressed in Modules One through Four.15600:10:01,274 --> 00:10:04,874I will now hand you over to Doctor Paul Milligan15700:10:05,058 --> 00:10:08,221and Doctor  Corine Merle who coordinated15800:10:08,403 --> 00:10:12,028this fifth module and they bring it to life15900:10:12,209 --> 00:10:13,721by bringing together a range16000:10:13,890 --> 00:10:16,202of stakeholders and community members16100:10:16,394 --> 00:10:19,944who have applied all of these principles in practice.16200:10:20,159 --> 00:10:23,159Of particular relevance are the discussions16300:10:23,353 --> 00:10:25,703about what is required in the scale-up16400:10:25,872 --> 00:10:29,472of your implementation research within your setting16500:10:29,673 --> 00:10:32,911or with broader application elsewhere.16600:10:33,262 --> 00:10:35,774Thank you for staying with us this far.16700:10:35,949 --> 00:10:38,749I sincerely hope it's been worth your while.16800:10:38,91